</p>
	  
	  
	  
	  
	  
	  
	  
<p>
      The department consists of 23 tenured and tenure-track faculty members most of them with active research programs and many with external funding. 
      Members of the department have research expertise in diverse areas such as mathematical finance, graph theory and combinatorics, mathematical biology, 
      fluid dynamics, stochastic calculus, and foundations of quantum mechanics.
</p>
       
<p>
